results.occurrenceRemarks: Five Four-Banded Sandgrouse nicely camouflaged in the dry grass alongside an interior road on the ICRISAT Sahelian Center research station at Sadore, approximately 40 km south-southeast of Niamey, Niger (5 km east of the Niamey-Say highway, N27). The group appears to be comprised of one male and four females.
